    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2902" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕκηλος</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝεκ</span>.) and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εὔκηλος</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">of good cheer, free from care, at ease;</span> often
          negatively, ‘undisturbed,’ ‘unmolested,’ <i><span class="en">Il.
            6.70</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 17.340</span></i>; iron.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕκηλος ἐρρέτω</span>, ‘let him go to
          perdition at his leisure,’ <i><span class="en">Il.
          9.376</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
